    fields:
      transcription: |-
        「お小遣い、この間1万円あげたでしょ。もうなくなったなんて、変だわ。何に使ったの」
        それは月給が少ないからよ。月給が多ければ、そんなこと言わないわ。
      meaning: |-
        Husband [mimicking his wife’s voice]: “I just gave you ¥10,000 in spending money. How could it vanish so quickly? What did you spend it on?”
        Wife: That’s because your salary is too low. I wouldn’t speak to you in that way if you were given a better salary.
    tags:
      - iij09
  - id: 0a443604-e9db-4a99-8281-4cdd59f9bf72
    start: 00:51.48
    end: 01:00.28
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        「今日は残業がないはずよ。どうしてこんなに遅いの」
        それは晩御飯が無駄になるからよ。
        分かった。
      meaning: |-
        Husband [mimicking his wifeis voice again]: “You weren’t supposed to have any overtime work today. What kept you out so late?”
        Wife: I just don’t want to waste your supper, that’s all.
        Husband: Okay, I get it.
    tags: *a1
  - id: 4b8d0d0f-640b-45d9-984d-6e162e2a8939
    start: 01:01.14
    end: 01:11.78
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        もう、そんなこと言うのやめるわ。
        それはありがたい。
        お小遣いは1000円ずつ渡す。
        おいおい。
        晩御飯は帰るまで作らないことにするわ。
      meaning: |-
        Wife: I won’t say those things to you ever again.
        Husband: Thank god.
        Wife: Henceforth, I’ll give you ¥1,000 at a time in spending money...
        Husband: Oh, no!
        Wife: And I won’t start cooking dinner till you’ve walked through the door.   
    tags: *a1
