clips:
  - id: 23a76103-a17d-41a6-b401-65fabcbeef06
    start: 04:09.208
    end: 04:14.148
    fields:
      transcription: 子供が習いたいと言うので、ピアノを{{c1::習わせる}}ことにした。
      meaning: Since the child said they wanted to learn, we decided to let them learn.
    tags:
      &a1
      - mimi_kara_grammar_n3
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: e9ae222d-a69f-4803-b346-40b4b807cb1b
    start: 04:21.887
    end: 04:27.047
    fields:
      transcription: 冷蔵庫に肉があるのを忘れていて、{{c1::腐らせて}}しまった。
      meaning: They forgot there was meat in the refrigerator, and let it go bad.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 5acf2b11-1a3c-4c7a-b608-1ddd68ab7153
    start: 04:39.703
    end: 04:44.943
    fields:
      transcription: 「すみません、体調が悪いので、早く{{c1::帰らせて}}ください」
      meaning: Excuse me, I'm not feeling very well, so please allow me to go home early.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 061577de-f011-4cc0-a1f6-b7082ace4d3d
    start: 04:52.963
    end: 04:58.543
    fields:
      transcription: 「今日は素晴らしいお話を{{c1::聞かせて頂き}}、本当にありがとうございます」
      meaning: Thanks so much for allowing us to hear your amazing story.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 6fa414af-8e2a-44a0-8e30-b855cf66dc4d
    start: 05:49.183
    end: 05:54.303
    fields:
      transcription: 道が混んでいる。これでは間に合わないのではないだろうか。
      meaning: The road is packed. We won't make it, don't you think?
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 82aac03a-7f50-4b45-9a5d-a782bf17c110
    start: 06:07.611
    end: 06:13.951
    fields:
      transcription: 「木村さん、遅いね」「もしかしたら、約束を忘れているんじゃない？」
      meaning: "\"Kimura is late, huh?\" \"He must have forgotten about the appointment, don't you think?\""
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: c71ea2e3-5c74-4981-9d9d-14485b92730b
    start: 07:50.015
    end: 07:56.327
    fields:
      transcription: この辺りでは、４月から５月{{c1::にかけて}}色々な花が咲く。
      meaning: In this area, lots of different flowers bloom from April all through till May.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: e5d3ec7f-81a3-4415-9046-a1ea8a4fafa2
    start: 08:25.087
    end: 08:30.463
    fields:
      transcription: 仕事が早く済んだのは、友達が手伝ってくれた{{c1::おかげ}}だ。
      meaning: The way I finished work early is thanks to my friend helping me.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: e592289f-e56d-48ed-89ae-f0be558f4af1
    start: 08:43.007
    end: 08:46.591
    fields:
      transcription: あの人のせいでみんなが迷惑している。
      meaning: Everyone is bothered because of him.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: e3e3615e-c66c-4421-97d2-66a110641512
    start: 08:57.087
    end: 09:01.439
    fields:
      transcription: 気のせいか、最近父は元気がないようだ。
      meaning: It might be [because] my imagination, but my father doesn't seem well lately.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 490783a2-ef6d-4663-bcaf-4dfb0dbfbe62
    start: 09:53.407
    end: 09:57.747
    fields:
      transcription: 「申し込み手続きに関してお伺いしたいのですが」
      meaning: I'd like to ask about the application process.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 17dd7b2f-66fa-4ea0-8258-1e0727194c0d
    start: 10:11.071
    end: 10:15.423
    fields:
      transcription: 昼間に比べて、深夜は電気料金が安い。
      meaning: Compared with the daytime, the electricity costs are cheap late at night.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: c82532ec-5274-441e-9df5-51871077d81d
    start: 10:48.211
    end: 10:55.051
    fields:
      transcription: あの二人は双子なのに、兄は大人しい{{c1::のに対して}}、弟はよく喋る。
      meaning: Even though those two are twins, in contrast with the elder brother's being quiet, the younger brother talks a lot.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: bff16428-513e-4d91-a38d-47af7a102c33
    start: 11:27.103
    end: 11:32.223
    fields:
      transcription: たとえ少々高くても、質の良いものが買いたい。
      meaning: Even if, say, it's a bit more expensive, I want to buy something of better quality.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 8eab0e92-65c6-4493-b3e6-df14bb7af6fc
    start: 12:17.535
    end: 12:20.607
    fields:
      transcription: 風邪{{c1::くらいで}}仕事を休めない。
      meaning: I can't take off work because of something as small as a cold.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 1bcaff61-6dfa-4f98-8a0f-4df742b95a4e
    start: 12:35.199
    end: 12:40.319
    fields:
      transcription: 途中でやめる{{c1::くらいなら}}、初めからやらないほうがいい。
      meaning: Rather than quitting in the middle, it would be better to hold off from the start.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 776019b9-7d65-41c0-8881-910e3e46b64c
    start: 13:29.527
    end: 13:37.147
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        駅前{{c1::を中心に}}再開発が進められ、新しいビルが次々と
        建てられている。
      meaning: The redevelopment has been carried forward with a focus on the front of the station, and new buildings are being built one after the other.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 59d47bce-d729-46aa-aea2-0e35621eb1a4
    start: 13:50.471
    end: 13:56.971
    fields:
      transcription: 最近の携帯電話にはカメラをはじめとして、色々な機能が付いている。
      meaning: Recent cell phones come with various features, such as a camera.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: bde85650-fab8-4482-9119-e41b05c9790c
    start: 14:28.607
    end: 14:33.215
    fields:
      transcription: 近代工業はヨーロッパにおいて誕生した。
      meaning: Modern-day industry was born in Europe.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: f49cc597-cf96-4cfd-9bef-abb729d283d8
    start: 14:48.319
    end: 14:54.463
    fields:
      transcription: 国立競技場では２週間{{c1::にわたって}}熱戦が繰り広げられた。
      meaning: In the national stadium, a fierce fight unfolded over the span of two weeks.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: a0112ac7-5a13-43aa-b8bb-ac79c83fd76f
    start: 15:34.911
    end: 15:39.519
    fields:
      transcription: 今度の台風{{c1::による}}被害は１億円に上る。
      meaning: The damages from the recent typhoon are up to 100 million yen.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 04b46438-0869-4e32-a4aa-08e62e059e04
    start: 15:47.199
    end: 15:51.039
    fields:
      transcription: 電話{{c1::による}}お問い合わせはご遠慮ください。
      meaning: Please refrain from making any enquiries via telephone.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 964fb63f-8a78-4d67-8403-7311c29a8b07
    start: 17:21.919
    end: 17:26.015
    fields:
      transcription: 一口食べた{{c1::途端}}、まずくて吐き出した。
      meaning: The moment I took a bite, [I found it] so bad I [had to] spit it out.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 4b3235cf-4a69-4fa1-91ed-23e58165e4f2
    start: 17:38.815
    end: 17:43.935
    fields:
      transcription: 試験が近づく{{c1::につれて}}、だんだん心配になってきた。
      meaning: As the test came nearer, I got more and more worried.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 1ec4abde-be4c-4a77-9fe6-836bcd68a5e0
    start: 17:59.039
    end: 18:04.415
    fields:
      transcription: 北半球では北へ行く{{c1::にしたがって}}気温が下がる。
      meaning: In the northern hemisphere, as you go north, the temperature drops.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 552f642d-f08e-4214-80d8-e5bf31d518a3
    start: 18:17.727
    end: 18:22.591
    fields:
      transcription: 着替えをしている{{c1::最中に}}玄関のチャイムが鳴った。
      meaning: As I was in the midst of changing clothes, the entrance doorbell rang.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: be98155a-ae1b-4b83-bbe0-3f4a25e65c51
    start: 18:40.255
    end: 18:45.375
    fields:
      transcription: 実物を見{{c1::てからでないと}}買うかどうかは決められない。
      meaning: Only once you've seen the real thing can you decide whether or not to buy it.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 0f3ba21c-29d6-4046-8e72-3f482bd123bd
    start: 18:58.175
    end: 19:04.063
    fields:
      transcription: 日本へ来{{c1::て以来}}、忙しくてまだ一度も帰国していない。
      meaning: Ever since coming to Japan, I've been so busy I haven't traveled home [to my country of origin] even once.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: d5c63493-d5d8-4ae6-9632-16ec134adc09
    start: 19:17.119
    end: 19:23.263
    fields:
      transcription: 不況のせいで収入が減った。貯金も減る{{c1::一方}}だ。
      meaning: Because of the recession, my income decreased. My savings just kept decreasing, too.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 4b0d76f4-a451-4949-91b5-60d3bbe79f8e
    start: 20:24.499
    end: 20:29.539
    fields:
      transcription: 用事で都心へ出た{{c1::ついでに}}、美術館を覗いてみた。
      meaning: Since I went out to the city center for something I had to take care of, I went ahead and had a look at the museum while I was at it.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 33050b26-28d8-4fc2-9373-5de65aadf92c
    start: 21:18.464
    end: 21:23.84
    fields:
      transcription: 「時間は十分にあるから、そんなに急ぐことはありませんよ」
      meaning: We have enough time, so you don't have to hurry like that.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 6973e01e-787c-4c75-9584-ee7bc32025d5
    start: 21:36.384
    end: 21:41.76
    fields:
      transcription: 明日は8時までに来ること。時間に遅れないこと。
      meaning: Come tomorrow at 8. Don't be late.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: f3859251-3175-4926-8442-0f06455482dd
    start: 21:57.12
    end: 22:02.24
    fields:
      transcription: 無理をすれば買えないこともないが、やはりやめておこう。
      meaning: While it's not as though I couldn't buy it if I pushed myself, but I'll hold off anyway.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3b0c7689-d82e-48bd-8262-3da08b7dda1a
    start: 22:36.644
    end: 22:44.424
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        「なぜ遅刻したのですか」
        「すみません、事故で電車が止まってしまった{{c1::ものですから}}」
      meaning: |-
        Why were you tardy?
        I'm sorry, it's because the train stopped because of an accident, you see.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: ac019cf3-0bb3-4ba7-b933-a4ec8259adf7
    start: 22:57.02
    end: 23:00.34
    fields:
      transcription: あんなまずい店、二度と行く{{c1::ものか}}。
      meaning: As if I'd go to such a bad restaurant again!
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 8993459d-b319-40a1-ac94-2a3a2dfc454a
    start: 23:13.152
    end: 23:18.528
    fields:
      transcription: 先生にお願い{{c1::したところ}}、快く引き受けてくださった。
      meaning: Once I had asked the teacher, he willingly accepted.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 1d6291ed-e468-4fb4-838f-20d028039e77
    start: 23:36.96
    end: 23:41.312
    fields:
      transcription: 家を出ようと{{c1::したところに}}電話がかかってきた。
      meaning: Right as I was about to leave the house, I got a phone call.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 24c98cbc-bd60-4aee-84db-d27e708bd8c1
    start: 23:54.112
    end: 24:00.256
    fields:
      transcription: 出かける時急いでいたので、もう少しで財布を{{c1::忘れるところだった}}。
      meaning: Since I was in a rush when I was setting out, I came this close to forgetting my wallet.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 09681963-5cd2-4b0b-be40-d6862ca3d902
    start: 24:08.14
    end: 24:13.28
    fields:
      transcription: あと少しで書き{{c1::終わるところだった}}のに、ベルが鳴ってしまった。
      meaning: I was just about to finish writing, but the bell rang on me.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: bbfda833-1194-43c5-8d8e-60a6b6bcfca2
    start: 24:26.112
    end: 24:28.928
    fields:
      transcription: 夜も眠れないほど悩んだ。
      meaning: I was so troubled I couldn't even sleep at night.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3323228d-6690-4872-b311-cef5919f3c9f
    start: 24:36.608
    end: 24:40.96
    fields:
      transcription: "{{c1::これほど}}面白い本は今まで読んだことがない。"
      meaning: I've never read such an interesting book as this.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 28a32e44-42be-40a0-8a79-669c813dedf9
    start: 24:54.528
    end: 25:00.416
    fields:
      transcription: 外国語は誰でも、練習すればするほど上手になる。
      meaning: When it comes to foreign languages, anyone will get better the more they practice.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 1684cde8-50ac-4477-95ae-070ce5209c79
    start: 25:12.96
    end: 25:16.8
    fields:
      transcription: 魚は新鮮なものほど美味しい。
      meaning: Fish is tastier the fresher it is.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 0961a9b1-8331-473d-9f66-f7f9518081fa
    start: 26:06.976
    end: 26:10.304
    fields:
      transcription: 彼が犯人{{c1::だなんて}}信じられない。
      meaning: I can't believe he would be a thief.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: cf724ca3-21cc-4f57-897c-016f49dd1004
    start: 26:22.848
    end: 26:27.2
    fields:
      transcription: 「やると決めた{{c1::からには}}最後まで頑張るつもりです」
      meaning: Now that I've decided to do it, I plan on doing my best until the end.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 9a5f01b3-7a41-43b4-933c-455f2be45d14
    start: 26:39.488
    end: 26:45.12
    fields:
      transcription: 全員力を{{c1::出し切って}}戦ったが、試合には負けてしまった。
      meaning: Everyone fought with all their strength, but they ended up losing the fight.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 0c614180-7747-4ad0-8821-1bd4479f83ed
    start: 26:53.056
    end: 26:57.152
    fields:
      transcription: 「あなたならできる」と母は{{c1::言い切った}}。
      meaning: '"You of all people can do it," asserted Mom.'
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 107c085f-c0e5-4f77-9d6b-ca27c8a04160
    start: 27:09.696
    end: 27:13.792
    fields:
      transcription: この２、３日、風邪{{c1::気味}}で調子が悪い。
      meaning: These two or three days, I've been in bad shape because of a slight cold.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: c33cf116-c65d-49f0-a03d-dca3844b8849
    start: 27:26.592
    end: 27:30.944
    fields:
      transcription: 年のせいか、母は最近病気{{c1::がち}}だ。
      meaning: Perhaps because of her age, my mother has been prone to getting sick lately.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: f809c190-6909-4de8-9c9b-23a78a421a7d
    start: 27:43.232
    end: 27:50.592
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        最近、職業に関しては、男性向きとか女性向きとか
        言えなくなってきた。
      meaning: Lately, with regard to occupations, you're no longer able to say "for men" or "for women".
    tags:
      - mimi_kara_grammar_n3
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3bd326e0-2521-4e27-8c4e-5fbac60debd4
    start: 28:03.2
    end: 28:08.32
    fields:
      transcription: この工場では主に{{c1::アメリカ向けの}}車を作っている。
      meaning: In this factory, they're making chiefly cars for America.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 416990a6-6ba1-41ed-80fa-0101b9c808e8
    start: 28:16.0
    end: 28:22.144
    fields:
      transcription: 来週のスピーチコンテスト{{c1::に向けて}}、毎日１時間以上練習している。
      meaning: For the purpose of next week's speech contest, I'm practicing more than one hour a day.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3e1ef21b-2173-4fda-85b3-e50900e444fb
    start: 28:36.736
    end: 28:40.832
    fields:
      transcription: 彼女とはサークルの先輩{{c1::を通して}}知り合った。
      meaning: I made her acquaintance through a senior member of the club.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 64d52cdb-ccb2-46f8-864e-9522b8a781e6
    start: 28:48.512
    end: 28:53.376
    fields:
      transcription: 京都には{{c1::年間を通じて}}、観光客が訪れる。
      meaning: In Kyoto, tourists visit throughout the year.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3f7e46c6-3640-4867-a302-209cfe466953
    start: 29:48.416
    end: 29:53.792
    fields:
      transcription: 日本語のレベルが上がる{{c1::とともに}}、勉強が楽しくなってきた。
      meaning: As my Japanese level went up, studying got more fun.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 5689f762-23f2-4e7b-8b78-9f7d35af6414
    start: 30:08.64
    end: 30:13.76
    fields:
      transcription: 会社の倒産{{c1::に伴って}}、多くの社員が失業した。
      meaning: With the company's bankruptcy, many employees lost their jobs.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: c0d92c1c-ebc7-4293-862a-d9771c2e0723
    start: 30:29.632
    end: 30:33.728
    fields:
      transcription: 「そんなの嘘に決まっている。信じられない」
      meaning: That's definitely a lie. I can't believe it.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 7a1d3ee6-4f7e-4090-b3f2-75242fe46945
    start: 31:15.456
    end: 31:21.344
    fields:
      transcription: 「皆さん、今から私が{{c1::言うように}}体を動かしてください」
      meaning: '"Everyone, moving forward, please move your bodies as I say."'
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: e9951bef-decc-4ce5-bfb1-d1fcf4d47cff
    start: 31:29.024
    end: 31:33.888
    fields:
      transcription: ９時の新幹線に間に{{c1::合うように}}、８時に家を出た。
      meaning: In order to make the 9 o'clock bullet train, I left the house at 8.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 056848df-dd40-440c-9d4e-3f058719e838
    start: 31:46.944
    end: 31:53.856
    fields:
      transcription: 手紙に彼の住所が書いてない。これでは返事の{{c1::出しようがない}}。
      meaning: He didn't write his address on the letter. There's no way to respond like this.
    tags:
      - mimi_kara_grammar_n3
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3bee7c76-b0cd-43a5-84c1-ed0209b2b0a2
    start: 32:06.4
    end: 32:10.496
    fields:
      transcription: ドアが開かない{{c1::はずだ}}。鍵が違っていた。
      meaning: So that means the door won't open. The key was the wrong one.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 83668beb-371a-4642-8310-661b2501c5b3
    start: 32:53.052
    end: 33:02.172
    fields:
      transcription: 私は毎日8時間寝ている。つまり、人生の３分の１をベッドで過ご{{c1::すわけだ}}。
      meaning: I spend 8 hours a day sleeping. So, that means I spend 1/3 of my life in bed.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: a18b3429-2fe3-4e91-8f88-a529a31366d1
    start: 33:09.888
    end: 33:14.24
    fields:
      transcription: テレビがつかない{{c1::わけだ}}。コンセントが抜けている。
      meaning: The TV won't turn on, then. The plug has come out.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 797468e8-471e-43d5-a0c6-1da5e04b0602
    start: 33:42.912
    end: 33:48.544
    fields:
      transcription: この問題はまだ習っていないのだから、{{c1::できるわけがない}}。
      meaning: I haven't learned this problem yet, so there's no way I can do it.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 4f93752a-9268-4417-9404-b598093a5dbc
    start: 34:01.6
    end: 34:06.464
    fields:
      transcription: 日本人が皆、日本文化に詳し{{c1::いわけではない}}。
      meaning: All Japanese people aren't necessarily that knowledgable about Japanese culture.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 32754e61-69b8-4afc-8bb4-5f8ce11d704b
    start: 34:19.776
    end: 34:25.152
    fields:
      transcription: 明日は大事な試験があるから休{{c1::むわけにはいかない}}。
      meaning: I have an important test tomorrow, so it's not like I can afford to take a break.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: ebc5f3dd-55a7-4e50-935a-eac176f9474b
    start: 34:38.976
    end: 34:44.096
    fields:
      transcription: 行くと約束したからには、行{{c1::かないわけにはいかない}}だろう。
      meaning: Since I promised I'd go, it's not like I can just not go.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: d22aefad-e0d2-403c-beb4-9dfd3941a390
    start: 35:25.824
    end: 35:31.712
    fields:
      transcription: あの店は味も雰囲気もいい{{c1::かわり}}、値段も安くはない。
      meaning: That restaurant has good food and a nice atmosphere, sure, but it's not cheap.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: b84ab10b-e6d2-4d9e-a060-ca2798eb2a20
    start: 35:44.768
    end: 35:49.376
    fields:
      transcription: 入院中の母{{c1::に代わって}}、姉が家事をしている。
      meaning: In place of our mom, who's in the hospital, my older sister is doing the housework.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 2dad48c4-d404-4147-852b-7f438c0b6dff
    start: 36:54.4
    end: 36:59.008
    fields:
      transcription: 痩せている{{c1::からといって}}、体が弱いとは限らない。　
      meaning: They may be thin, but that doesn't mean they're weak.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: b285201f-e9ba-4939-a883-0ac25847451f
    start: 37:06.688
    end: 37:11.04
    fields:
      transcription: 寒い{{c1::からといって}}、家にばかりいるのは良くない。
      meaning: You can say it's cold, but it's not good to just stay at home.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3bedc61d-e262-46cb-84a6-fd2f4f558df8
    start: 37:24.096
    end: 37:29.984
    fields:
      transcription: A チームが勝つだろうという予想{{c1::に反して}}、B チームが勝った。
      meaning: Contrary to the expectation that Team A would win, Team B won.
    tags:
      - mimi_kara_grammar_n3
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 0e4f877e-67a2-4ef0-8117-9f4b0ff864be
    start: 37:45.344
    end: 37:50.464
    fields:
      transcription: この映画は実際にあった事件{{c1::に基づいて}}作られた。
      meaning: This movie was made on the basis of an incident that truly happened.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 1e1d1368-27e3-4d99-9f85-c7096499e716
    start: 38:03.52
    end: 38:08.384
    fields:
      transcription: この映画は実際にあった事件{{c1::をもとに}}作られた。
      meaning: This movie was made based on on an incident that truly happened.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 6c299875-6bec-436b-ba0d-a41bc3c3a7a9
    start: 38:21.184
    end: 38:27.072
    fields:
      transcription: この新しい薬はよく{{c1::効く反面}}、副作用も強い。
      meaning: While the new medicine is effective, on the other hand, the side effects are strong.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3a4b6cc4-16d2-4b69-9de5-8a2d5f9455ca
    start: 38:58.816
    end: 39:02.912
    fields:
      transcription: 会いた{{c1::くてたまらない}}のに会えないのは辛い。
      meaning: It's tough not being able to see you, even though I miss you so much I can't bear it.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 99b3c894-3ede-4a5b-af78-a030c575ddbf
    start: 39:15.968
    end: 39:20.832
    fields:
      transcription: 希望通りの会社に就職でき、嬉し{{c1::くてならない}}。
      meaning: I'm ever so happy to have acquired a post at the company I was hoping.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: b0bdc641-3bf2-4836-b6df-c7076a95be6e
    start: 39:52.832
    end: 39:56.416
    fields:
      transcription: 試験が終わったら、好き{{c1::なだけ}}遊びたい。
      meaning: Once the test is over, enjoy yourself however you like.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 0f7e411e-bae9-439c-a309-186812e4cffd
    start: 40:09.472
    end: 40:14.336
    fields:
      transcription: 彼女は英語{{c1::ばかりでなく}}、フランス語やドイツ語も話せる。
      meaning: She can speak not only English, but also French and German.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 6c303931-f9b7-4e48-951e-fe066c03dfb8
    start: 40:28.16
    end: 40:31.744
    fields:
      transcription: 「{{c1::やりかけた}}ことは最後までちゃんとやりなさい」
      meaning: What you've done part-way, please do properly till the end.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: c091d747-43ca-4c9c-810c-c1ede1dd5e37
    start: 40:44.544
    end: 40:49.408
    fields:
      transcription: 母の誕生日に、{{c1::心を込めて}}編んだセーターを贈った。
      meaning: For my mother's birthday, I gave her as a present a sweater I knitted with all my heart.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: ae46a822-2eb1-430c-aa60-c80022484e68
    start: 41:01.952
    end: 41:08.096
    fields:
      transcription: 「山田さんは、留学経験がない{{c1::割に}}英語の発音が綺麗ですね。」
      meaning: For someone who doesn't have any experience studying abroad,  his English pronunciation is very clear.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 68edde14-7f35-4d09-b39f-8283a7291dfb
    start: 41:20.64
    end: 41:24.992
    fields:
      transcription: 母は歌が下手{{c1::なくせに}}、マイクを持つと離さない。
      meaning: Even though my mother is bad at singing, once she gets a hold of the mic, she won't let go.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 3a82a147-cd61-40f3-8c2c-64e8e72de032
    start: 41:37.536
    end: 41:44.448
    fields:
      transcription: 言葉で説明するのが難しいことでも、実際に{{c1::やって見せれば}}すぐにわかる。
      meaning: It's hard to explain in words, but once you try it out in real life, you'll get it right away.
    tags:
      - mimi_kara_grammar_n3
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 85d52933-a519-42e7-9b8c-0966b49502d1
    start: 42:13.631
    end: 42:17.983
    fields:
      transcription: 大学入学{{c1::をきっかけに}}、一人暮らしを始めた。
      meaning: Starting from when I got into college, I began living on my own.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 8522baf7-0cf9-4d7f-ad48-2485474d3238
    start: 42:30.527
    end: 42:38.627
    fields:
      transcription: 太陽を直径１メートルの球だ{{c1::とします}}。すると地球は９ミリくらいです。
      meaning: Suppose the sun were 1 meter in diameter. Then, the Earth would be about 9 millimeters.
    tags:
      - mimi_kara_grammar_n3
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 20284ea4-3ab5-40b4-a44e-e2436851ed72
    start: 42:52.799
    end: 42:56.895
    fields:
      transcription: お見舞いに行{{c1::くとしたら}}、何時頃がいいだろうか。
      meaning: Supposing we were to go see them [in the hospital], what time would be good?
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: 84cb2363-1e76-462a-995a-80b46a62ca7a
    start: 43:07.391
    end: 43:14.235
    fields:
      transcription: チャレンジ精神こそ大切だ。もし失敗{{c1::したとしても}}後悔はしないぞ。
      meaning: A challenger's spirit is key. Even if I were to lose, I'll have no regrets!
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: b2e1ead3-6f01-43cf-94f0-76705a5da289
    start: 43:28.895
    end: 43:34.271
    fields:
      transcription: 「今度日本へいらっしゃ{{c1::った際には}}、是非我が家にお泊りください」
      meaning: Next time you come to Japan, by all means, please stay at my home.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
  - id: bb3ab505-fa03-4dfd-b039-84a805c4bbc7
    start: 43:47.071
    end: 43:52.447
    fields:
      transcription: この薬は副作用{{c1::の恐れがある}}ので、注意しなければならない。
      meaning: There's a danger of side effects with this medicine, so you must be careful.
    tags: *a1
    image:
      type: VideoStill
